@startuml C5_MLOpsPipeline
title MLOps Pipeline — Blue-Green Release Decision Flow

actor "Platform Engineer" as User
participant "Release Controller\n(FastAPI)" as RC
participant "Airflow" as AF
participant "Eval Service\n(FastAPI)" as Eval
participant "MLflow" as MLflow
database "PostgreSQL" as PG
participant "Prometheus" as Prom

== 1. Candidate Registration ==

User -> RC : POST /api/v1/releases\n{model, version, slot: "green"}
RC -> PG : INSERT release record\nstatus=registered
PG --> RC : release_id
RC --> User : {release_id, status: "registered"}

== 2. Automated Pipeline (Airflow) ==

User -> AF : Trigger release_decision_pipeline DAG
activate AF

== 2a. Evaluation ==
AF -> Eval : POST /api/v1/eval\n{release_id: blue}
Eval -> MLflow : Log params + metrics
MLflow --> Eval : run_id
Eval --> AF : blue_eval_metrics

AF -> Eval : POST /api/v1/eval\n{release_id: green}
Eval -> MLflow : Log params + metrics
Eval --> AF : green_eval_metrics

== 2b. Replay Comparison (parallel) ==
AF -> Eval : POST /api/v1/replay\n{blue_id, green_id}
Eval -> MLflow : Log comparison metrics
Eval --> AF : {blue_metrics, green_metrics, recommendation}

== 2c. Drift Detection (parallel) ==
AF -> Eval : POST /api/v1/drift\n{release_id: blue}
Eval -> Prom : Query production metrics
Prom --> Eval : Metric timeseries
Eval -> MLflow : Log drift scores
Eval --> AF : {drift_detected, drift_score}

== 3. Release Decision ==
AF -> RC : POST /api/v1/releases/decide\n{blue_id, green_id, auto_apply: false}
activate RC

RC -> PG : Fetch blue + green records
PG --> RC : Release records with eval_metrics

RC -> RC : Decision Engine evaluates:\n- Error rate gates\n- Quality score gates\n- Latency gates\n- Drift threshold\n- Improvement threshold

RC -> PG : Store decision + rationale
RC --> AF : {decision, rationale, applied: false}
deactivate RC

deactivate AF

== 4. Manual Review & Apply ==

User -> RC : GET /api/v1/releases\n(review decision)
RC --> User : decision: "switch_to_green"\nrationale: "Green passes all gates..."

note right of RC
  Decision outcomes:
  - stay_on_blue
  - switch_to_green
  - rollback_to_blue
  - hold_for_review

  Default: recommendation only
  (manual approval required)
end note

User -> RC : POST /api/v1/releases/decide\n{auto_apply: true}
RC -> PG : Update: green=active, blue=archived
RC --> User : {decision: "switch_to_green", applied: true}

== Storage Map ==

note over PG
  Stores:
  - Release registry (status, slot)
  - Decision rationale
  - Eval metrics snapshot
end note

note over MLflow
  Stores:
  - Evaluation experiments
  - Replay comparisons
  - Drift detection runs
  - Metrics artifacts
end note

note over Prom
  Stores:
  - Live production metrics
  - Latency, error rates
  - Resource utilization
end note

@enduml
